Class FuzzySet

  • java.lang.Object
    • fif_core.FuzzySet

  • public class FuzzySet
extends java.lang.Object
    This class provides implementation and methods of a fuzzy set.

    It can be instantiate a fuzzy set without values.

      • getValue

        public double getValue(java.lang.String element)
        Get the membershipvalue associated to the input element.

        Preconditions:

        1-The element can't be null.

        Postconditions:

        1-It's returned a value between 0 and 1 if the element exists and the value is mapped, 0 otherwise.

        Parameters:
        element - The identification value of the couple.
        Returns:
        the membership value associated to the element.

      • setValue

        public void setValue(java.lang.String element,
                     double membershipValue)
        Set a specific couple of values for this fuzzy set.

        Preconditions:

        1-The element can't be null.
        2-The membership value should be between 0 and 1.

        Postconditions:

        1-The couple of values is set correctly.

        Parameters:
        element - The identification value of the couple.
        membershipValue - The fuzzy value of the couple.
